task.summary: Initial commit - have got the compiler parsing a source file, not sure how well it works, but do have some output of sorts that looks like the compiler has done a transformation.

Awesome - have got position information and code snippets by walking the tree. So much easier with the Scala presentation compiler than the F# compiler - although to be fair, I have yet to check the positions I've got - do they reflect the original source or the internal representation of the AST? Not a bad start, though...
More awesome things - now got a tree structure of positions from the parse tree.
First very uneasy steps with using scalaz-streams to implement the plugin driver logic. Hmm....
